pageContext.claim: “We expect to have 100 million doses of vaccine available. And certainly, before the end of the year, but we think we're going to have therapeutically or through vaccine, something announced long before even that.”
pageContext.analysis: Dr. Moncef Slaoui, head of Operation Warp Speed, told NPR that he estimated about 20 to 30 million doses of a vaccine — not 100 million — would be ready by the end of the year.
